&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;MATERNITY SUPPORT WORKER FOR EVESHAM COMMUNITY MIDWIVES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Evesham Community Midwives are looking for an enthusiastic and organized maternity support worker to join our small friendly team. The successful candidate will be required to support the community midwives in all aspects of their work as well as working independently running their own phlebotomy clinic and providing administration back up. The ideal candidate will have a general understanding of maternity services in the area, will have had some experience of the computer systems the Trust uses, and be phlebotomy trained. However full training will be given.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Claire Layton, Team Leader on clairelayton@nhs.net or 07553379412.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
